# Hyperledger Fabric Project(Supplychain)

This repository contains a Hyperledger Fabric project. The project includes configurations and necessary files to set up and run a Hyperledger Fabric network.

## Project Structure
project-root/
├── .gitignore
├── README.md
├── configtx/
├── crypto-config/
├── channel-artifacts/
├── docker-compose.yaml
├── node_modules/
├── dist/
├── build/
├── .env
├── msp/
├── tls/
├── .vscode

## Installation

### Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed:

- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/)
- [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)
- [Node.js and npm](https://nodejs.org/) (if your project includes Node.js components)

### Steps

1. **Clone the Repository**

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
   cd your-repo-name

   #npm install
   run this to install the node modeule dependecnies
2. **Generate Crypto Material and Configuration Files **
   cryptogen generate --config=./crypto-config.yaml
   configtxgen -profile SampleMultiNodeEtcdRaft -outputBlock ./channel-artifacts/genesis.block -channelID system-channel
   configtxgen -profile SampleMultiNodeEtcdRaft -outputCreateChannelTx ./channel-artifacts/channel.tx -channelID mychannel
3. Start the Network
   docker-compose -f docker-compose.yaml up -d

4. Create and Join the Channel
   docker exec -it cli bash
   peer channel create -o orderer.example.com:7050 -c mychannel -f ./channel-artifacts/channel.tx
   peer channel join -b mychannel.block
